As Xany wrote to Dr. Math
On 08/10/2004 at 15:05:47 (Eastern Time),
>[Question]
>Hi, my question is: what is the converse of the multiplication 
>property of zero? I understand that the multiplication property of 
>zero is a*0=0=0*a, but how can you converse that? 
>PLease help me, Thank you
>
>[Difficulty]
>
>
>[Thoughts]
>

Hi Xany,

Given

  P -> Q

the converse is

  Q -> P

So if we state the multiplication property of zero this way, 

  (x = 0) -> (for all a, ax = xa = x)

then the converse is

  (for all a, ax = xa = x) -> (x = 0)

Does that make sense? 

